snippet.textDisplay:
With sausage making with the casings, always make sure your casings are wet so that they don't get stuck and rip when feeding the meat through.

If you like a fatter sausage, I recommend pork casings over sheep/lamb/whatever.

If you are doing a larger number of sausages, make sure you wet your work surface, again, to ensure your sausages are going to tear or stick too much.
